                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Dec. 22 (PTI): The Centre has issued an advisory to state governments asking them to prevent misuse of the dowry harassment law, the Rajya Sabha was informed today.          Under this law, the accused are immediately arrested without possibility of bail.           
	A number of representations have been received from various quarters regarding the misuse of the provisions of Section 498 A of the IPC (subjecting married women to cruelty), law minister M. Veerappa Moily said in a written reply.           
	Those found guilty under this law can be imprisoned for up to three years.                  
	 Washington (PTI): Twenty-eight Indian crew members on board a crippled bulk cargo freighter, which was stranded in mid-sea off the Alaska coast, are headed for their destination in Portland after the vessels engine was repaired. The crew of APJ Suryavir had planned to abandon the ship because of stormy weather.                  
	 New Delhi: Britain has invited India to a conference on Afghanistan to be held in London on Jauary 28 next year. British foreign secretary David Miliband invited external affairs minister S.M. Krishna over the telephone. British Prime Minister Gordon Brown is the prime mover behind the 68-nation conference on the future of Afghanistan.                  London (PTI) : The UK and the US have lodged a diplomatic protest with India after New Delhi introduced rules barring foreign tourists from returning to the country within two months of a visit. The rules are a reaction to the arrest of terror suspect David Headley.                   
	 Jaipur (PTI): A man who was allegedly trying to sneak into India from Pakistan was shot dead in the early hours of Tuesday by BSF jawans in Rajasthans Sriganganagar district. The man has not been identified. Jawans fired at the man, warning him to go back but he kept advancing, police said.
                                                                                                                                              
